headline: Deutsche Bank views partial decision on Arm, Qualcomm dispute as incremental
summary: Deutsche Bank notes that late on Dec 20th, a Delaware jury issued a partial decision on the IP dispute between Arm (ARM) and Hold-rated Qualcomm (QCOM), finding that the latter did not violate the architectural license granted to Nuvia and that Qualcomm’s existing architectural license with Arm allowed it to continue developing custom cores obtained via the Nuvia acquisition.
